overed Sicily from the Arabs. His son, also called Roger, ruled Sicily as king, presiding over a court noted for its splendour and patronage of the arts."],"variants":[{"name":"Rodger","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Roger  , in part from the surname derived from the given name in the Middle Ages."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705184,"age":2,"year":"1096","julianDay":2121366,"title":"The Crusades","description":"A series of religious wars between Christians and Muslims, known as the Crusades, occurred between 1096 and 1291, and played a large role in European Christian dominance in the Middle East.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/middle-ages/crusades","urlTitle":"History - The Crusades","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705185,"age":12,"year":"1106","julianDay":2125018,"title":"The Battle of Tichebray","description":"King Henry I defeated and captured his brother, Robert of Normandy, at the Battle of Tinchebray in 1106. Robert remained in captivity until his death in 1134.","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Roger de Kyme was born in 1094, in Kyme, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom as the son of Ralf De Kyme. He married wife Roger de Kyme before 1124, in Europe. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in 1162, in England, at the age of 68."},"et":{"1094–1162":"1094–1162","–Female":"Surnud","1124–Female":"1124–Surnud","1064–1130":"1064–1130","1106":"1106","BEF 1130":"enne 1130","Abt 1124":"umbes 1124","before 1124":"enne 1124","1124":"1124","1130":"1130","1064":"1064","1162":"1162","1096":"1096","1094":"1094","Europe":"Europe","England":"England","Kyme, Lincolnshire, England":"Kyme, Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1094–1162":"1094–1162","–Female":"Kuollut","1124–Female":"1124–Kuollut","1064–1130":"1064–1130","1106":"1106","BEF 1130":"ennen vuotta 1130","Abt 1124":"noin 1124","before 1124":"ennen vuotta 1124","1124":"1124","1130":"1130","1064":"1064","1162":